cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with network coding and authentication, which are closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of linear codes and subspace codes also suggests a connection to network security (cs.NI) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The introduction of access structure and the characterization of security by minimal codewords may also relate to information security (cs.SI).
